data.title: Brunch with friends
data.text: We drove over to Hampton to have Brunch with friends. It was their first visit. They will be back. It was absolutely delicious. They do unique twist on dishes that keep you coming back. The Ham,Biscuits and gravy with two over easy fried eggs were amazing. My wife loved her blackened Oyster's.Our friends had the Breakfast Quesadillas and The Ham,Biscuit and gravy  . We had the House Tater Tots and the fluffy Grits as sides. Over the top delicious. They open at 10 am and fill up very quickly.

data.title: Nov 1st,2016
data.text: First time visit.  Had the "meat-za" pizza (meat lovers) and it was great.   Just the right size for dinner.   Variety of drafts, wines, and cocktails available .   Courtney was my server and was friendly and polite.   Welcomed new addition to the area.   Reasonably priced, good food and drinks, in a casual atmosphere = winning formula in my book. I'll be back!!!

data.title: Night out with friends
data.text: Great food was had by the four of us. Collard greens, pork belly, meatballs, tater tots, Cobb salad, and two types of pizza. We all enjoyed everything.  Our waitress was top notch. We will definitely return.

data.title: Relaxing Restaurant - Great Staff - Very Good Dinner
data.text: Stopped in with friends - the staff were very welcoming and friendly.   Great pizza - delicious tuna and wonderful tater tots.  Great meal - Great service!!!  Hope to go back while we are in Hampton

data.title: Good food
data.text: Delicious food. Hard to get a seat because it is pretty small. Food is good. I wish they had not revamped their menu, there are items I really enjoyed. Worth a visit. Pizzas are also good.

data.title: Great place
data.text: We were with a group of 9 and had a great time. Jackie did a nice job of being helpful and courtious. We had pizzas and they were cooked to perfection. It was a wonderful place for vegetarians and we're happy we came.

data.title: Hit or miss flavors, good pizzas
data.text:
We recently tried Venture Kitchen for the first time & got take out.  The staff taking our order was quick, efficient, &our food was ready when we picked it up.  From the Tapas menu we got the pork meatballs – 3 for $5; they were covered in a Thai sweet chili glaze, and strips of fresh basil leaves.  Now, I am being serious & not exaggerating when I say that when I cut into the meatball it smelled like cat food.  I asked my husband to come over & while I hadn’t said anything about it, he said the same thing.  So, needless to say that was a big turnoff.  But, we tasted the meatball & it was okay.  It was a bit crumbly & didn’t hold together well.  The glaze/sauce was cloyingly sweet & the basil just made it sweeter.  It was a bit overpowering & not an appropriate accompaniment to the meatballs.  

Also from the Tapas menu we got the hibachi vegetables with a ginger buttermilk tarragon dipping sauce for $7.  The veggies were plentiful, but we were really hoping for a sear on them from the hibachi grill.  They seemed more steamed and were fairly bland.  We did not like the sauce as an appropriate accompaniment to these veggies.  The buttermilk was so strong the sauce made our mind go to ranch dressing/some mayo based dip.  I didn’t taste any ginger & the tarragon was just not strong enough to make the sauce balanced.  We dipped the veggies in the Thai sweet chili glaze from the meatballs & not even that was palatable.  The veggies were fine on their own after we added some badly needed seasoning. 

We had ordered after 4pm on a weekday; at that time only Tapas, salads, & pizzas are available.  We ordered 2 pizzas.  My husband got the sausage & peppers pizza, which he enjoyed.  I got the pesto mushroom pizza.  The crust was thin & crispy, which I liked.  The pesto was very flavorful and spread plentifully & evenly.  My favorite was the mushrooms – they were very flavorful, plump, juicy, & plentiful. 
      
The portions were appropriate for the price.  Venture Kitchen is appropriately named, as they are adventurous in their flavor combinations.  Some work, some need work.  It’s worth a visit to sample their menu; I don’t think we’d go out of our way to return….but we might come back some time to try more of their pizzas since ours were yummy.

data.title: Not the friendliest place.
data.text: I stood around for at least 3 to 5 minutes before anyone greeted me, but I was not made to feel welcomed in their establishment and I will never return.

data.title: The place for foodies in Hampton Roads
data.text: We've never had anything but great experiences here. Off-beat menus (for both dining and the bar) guarantee happy palates. If you're tentative, no need to worry. The staff knows what they're talking about and can guide you toward something you'll enjoy.

data.title: Great place
data.text: We were looking for a snack as we had dinner plans.  We saw the tapas, so gave it a try.  The portions are a bit larger than a true tapas, but the food was EXCELLENT.  A good selection of beers on tap. If you are in the area, definitely stop by.

data.title: A family favorite
data.text: Tapas, pizza, and an extensive( and interesting) full bar. You might wonder if this mix works- it does.  Venture is a comfortable and eclectic restaurant.  I labeled this review- A Family Favorite.  The family consists of 2 Baby Boomers, 2 Gen X Foodies and a family of 3 with a 4 year old- we all love it and it is one of our "Go To" spots.

data.title: Small and Exceptional
data.text:
I came to Venture based entirely on the Trip Advisor reviews. The local streets in this area of town are quite narrow with parking on one side. Don't be fooled, the streets are for two-way traffic.
My first impression was concerning because it is a very small place and the bar runs half its length. Seating is in booths so it wasn't cramped for dining but I expect a wait during busy times. The wait staff was friendly and helpful. Venture fare is primarily tapas and pizza with just a few entrées. I chose the "must have" tater tots, scallops, and seared tuna. The tater tots were good; I'm not a fan of fried foods and would have preferred them a little crispier; and the dipping sauce was very good. The scallops were exceptional! Probably the best I've ever eaten. The scallops were served on a bed of pasta with a light tomato sauce that was very good. The seared tuna was extremely good and very fresh. The seaweed salad that accompanied the tuna was interesting, fresh & crisp with a pickled flavor, and did not fit my tastes.
I will be back to Venture on future Hampton trips.

data.title: Great place to eat & drink
data.text: We visited this place during our stay in Hampton. Food and drinks were great and also our bartender Stefanie! Greetings from Czech Republic :)

data.title: The collards are the best I have ever eaten
data.text: This a very nice and respectable restaurant.  The service is great and the food is very good especially the collard greens (served at dinner).  They have a bar for those who drink not sure exactly the type of beer served because I don't drink.

data.title: Scallops to die for.
data.text: Stopped in on a whim for a lunch date with my husband and was completely blown away. Perfectly cooked scallops with creamy pesto orzo and chorizo.

data.title: Love love love
data.text: Great food and flavors . Nice bar . Great pizzas tapas are awesome . Staff are very attentive. Music is great. We have eaten here at leat three time in 3 days we will be back. Keep up the great work and continue to satisfy the taste buds.

data.title: Great lunch spot
data.text: New menu this week.  Spicy eggplant grinder was unbelievably good.  Great atmosphere and friendly people.

data.title: The Best Tapas in the Tidewater !
data.text: Venture Kitchen has been our Friday night go-to place for consistently great food and service. We have tried a variety of Tapas bars in the Tidewater area (Norfolk, Newport News, Virginia Beach, etc.) Venture is by far our favorite. The cheese board is one of our favorites. The cheeses are always well-chosen and excellent quality. We love the fried green tomatillos, but unfortunately they have not been on the menu this year. However, all their Tapas are delicious. Their pizzas are also excellent. My husband usually orders a pizza along with our shared Tapas. If you're looking for great cocktails, they can be a little disappointing. I ordered a mojito and when it arrived, I found there were cucumbers in it. This was not to my taste at all. It did not taste fresh. When I sent it back, the waitress told me that that is how mojitos are made in their restaurant. I have tried several other mixed drinks in Venture, but find that their bartender is not as talented as their chefs. I think the owner should invest in a well trained bar tender to boost drink sales. For drinks, we usually stick to beer or wine. However, since we usually only have one drink, it is not an issue for us. The food makes it well worthwhile. They also have nice roomy booths, which can fit a party of six, if you call ahead. I highly recommend a trip to Hampton, just to visit Venture Kitchen

data.title: Fun & great food
data.text: Tapas large enough to share, very creative.& good service. Best pizza on the peninsula. Dinner specials change every night at 5 pm.

data.title: Local variety
data.text: Lunches or dinners are of good quality and they offer a broad variety of choices to suit almost anybody. The place is friendly and the service is very good too.
